Package: tters
Title: Sequential Target Trial Emulation Data Expansion (Rust + Polars Backend)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Michael", "Batech", , "oldschoolcool@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fast, verified data-expansion stage for sequential target trial
    emulation, backed by a Rust and Polars engine via the 'extendr' crate.
    Reproduces, bit-for-bit, the expansion output of the 'TrialEmulation' R
    package. The heavy lifting lives in the 'tte-expand' Rust core crate; this
    package is a thin binding layer.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2)
Imports:
    bit64
Suggests:
    arrow,
    data.table,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    TrialEmulation
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/rextendr/version: 0.5.0
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc >= 1.95.0
URL: https://github.com/oldschoolcool2/rust-tte
BugReports: https://github.com/oldschoolcool2/rust-tte/issues
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
